14/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian Education Minister Azis Polozhani met with Bulgarian counterpart Daniel Valchev on Monday (13 March) and agreed to boost co-operation in the sector.
In particular, they discussed ways to harmonise higher educational standards in the two neighbouring states with those of the EU.
They also agreed that the two governments should work to remove any texts inciting hatred or violence.
(Trud - 14/03/06;
BNR, Telma TV, A1 TV - 13/03/06)
